Week 8 roundup: Around Northeast Florida high school football 
Sat, Oct 17, 2015 @ 12:16 am 
AROUND NORTHEAST FLORIDA 
Bradford (5-3, 2-1) surprised visiting Keystone Heights (5-2, 1-1) 28-14 in District 3-4A play... West Nassau (5-2, 1-1 District 2-4A) routed county rival Fernandina Beach (2-6, 1-2) 30-0... Oakleaf (6-1) scored six quick touchdowns and never looked back in a 42-3 rout of visiting Arlington Country Day (0-6)... Eagleâ€™s View (2-5, 1-2 District 2-2A) won 38-8 to keep visiting Harvest Community (0-7, 0-2) winless... Yulee (4-3, 1-1 District 3-5A) won 41-6 to extend the losing streak of Stanton (0-7, 0-2)... St. Johns Country Day (1-6) lost 35-0 at Gainesville Oak Hall (6-1).
